00:00:02.604 --> 00:00:03.638 position:21% line:89% align:start
[singing in Japanese]

00:01:11.706 --> 00:01:12.540 position:21% line:89% align:start
[singing in Japanese]

00:01:25.252 --> 00:01:28.690 position:10% line:83% align:start
[narrator] Life continues in
its usual manner

00:01:28.723 --> 00:01:30.424 position:19% line:89% align:start
on the strange island.

00:01:30.457 --> 00:01:33.360 position:16% line:83% align:start
Jean and Nadia discovered
an underground cavern

00:01:33.393 --> 00:01:35.830 position:35% line:83% align:start
filled with
alarmingly familiar objects.

00:01:35.863 --> 00:01:39.433 position:19% line:83% align:start
When Nadia's Blue Water
suddenly began to glow,

00:01:39.466 --> 00:01:44.371 position:10% line:83% align:start
she mysteriously disappeared
into a solid metal wall.

00:01:44.404 --> 00:01:46.473 position:24% line:89% align:start
Now listen closely,

00:01:46.507 --> 00:01:50.878 position:5% line:83% align:start
because the secret of Blue Water
shall now be revealed.

00:02:00.420 --> 00:02:01.589 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Sanson] Hey, Hanson,

00:02:01.623 --> 00:02:03.256 position:16% line:83% align:start
I need you to do whatever
you're doing later

00:02:03.290 --> 00:02:05.158 position:35% line:83% align:start
and come up
here and help me now.

00:02:05.192 --> 00:02:06.259 position:30% line:89% align:start
Just a minute.

00:02:07.962 --> 00:02:10.197 position:33% line:83% align:start
Will you stop
doodling in that book?

00:02:10.230 --> 00:02:11.532 position:7% line:89% align:start
Let's fix this thing right now

00:02:11.566 --> 00:02:12.800 position:16% line:83% align:start
and get off this wretched
land mass

00:02:12.834 --> 00:02:14.434 position:24% line:89% align:start
with all due haste.

00:02:15.603 --> 00:02:16.771 position:24% line:89% align:start
All right already.

00:02:18.806 --> 00:02:21.709 position:7% line:83% align:start
You really helped us fixed this
balloon in record time,

00:02:21.743 --> 00:02:22.810 position:33% line:89% align:start
my dear girl.

00:02:22.844 --> 00:02:24.277 position:21% line:89% align:start
So thank you, Marie.

00:02:24.311 --> 00:02:25.747 position:30% line:89% align:start
[chuckles] Huh?

00:02:26.748 --> 00:02:27.782 position:33% line:89% align:start
[King purrs]

00:02:31.251 --> 00:02:33.655 position:21% line:83% align:start
And thank you, King,
for all of your efforts.

00:02:36.423 --> 00:02:37.491 position:33% line:89% align:start
[King purrs]

00:02:38.626 --> 00:02:41.194 position:5% line:89% align:start
Nadia is pretty late, isn't she?

00:02:41.228 --> 00:02:43.598 position:33% line:89% align:start
[King purrs]

00:02:43.631 --> 00:02:45.767 position:27% line:83% align:start
Hmm, it's strange
that they'd get lost

00:02:45.800 --> 00:02:47.467 position:16% line:89% align:start
in the forest, isn't it?

00:02:47.502 --> 00:02:49.604 position:30% line:83% align:start
Jean is staying
pretty tightlipped about it.

00:02:49.637 --> 00:02:50.938 position:30% line:89% align:start
Most peculiar.

00:02:50.972 --> 00:02:52.907 position:35% line:83% align:start
And what's
that supposed to mean?

00:02:52.940 --> 00:02:55.777 position:16% line:83% align:start
Keep in mind that Jean's
not a reprobate like you are.

00:02:55.810 --> 00:02:57.712 position:19% line:89% align:start
Oh, no. Just a minute.

00:02:57.745 --> 00:03:00.982 position:10% line:83% align:start
I was simply referring to the
forest in which they got lost.

00:03:01.015 --> 00:03:03.518 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Hanson] Come to think of it,
there was something strange

00:03:03.551 --> 00:03:05.352 position:10% line:89% align:start
about the mountain yesterday.

00:03:05.385 --> 00:03:07.287 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Ouch.
-That's true.

00:03:07.320 --> 00:03:09.356 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm afraid there's
a terrible secret

00:03:09.389 --> 00:03:10.725 position:13% line:89% align:start
hidden within this island.

00:03:10.758 --> 00:03:12.593 position:41% line:89% align:start
I see.

00:03:12.627 --> 00:03:14.494 position:7% line:83% align:start
I wonder why Jean won't tell us
what he knows about it.

00:03:14.529 --> 00:03:15.997 position:33% line:89% align:start
I don't know.

00:03:16.030 --> 00:03:18.800 position:13% line:83% align:start
I guess it's just something
he can't talk to anyone about.

00:03:18.833 --> 00:03:20.802 position:35% line:89% align:start
[all] Hmm.

00:03:22.302 --> 00:03:23.705 position:30% line:89% align:start
All right then.

00:03:23.738 --> 00:03:25.673 position:27% line:83% align:start
I'm going to see
what's on the boy's mind.

00:03:25.707 --> 00:03:27.474 position:35% line:83% align:start
No, Sanson.
I think we should all try

00:03:27.508 --> 00:03:29.777 position:33% line:83% align:start
to leave him
alone for the time being.

00:03:29.811 --> 00:03:32.513 position:13% line:83% align:start
Don't worry about a thing.
I'll just go and cheer him up.

00:03:37.752 --> 00:03:38.886 position:35% line:89% align:start
Hey, Jean.

00:03:42.557 --> 00:03:43.791 position:16% line:83% align:start
-What's the matter, lad?
-Huh?

00:03:43.825 --> 00:03:44.726 position:21% line:89% align:start
You're not yourself.

00:03:46.060 --> 00:03:47.662 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Hmm.
-You know that Nadia is going

00:03:47.695 --> 00:03:49.362 position:16% line:89% align:start
to come back to us, Jean.

00:03:49.396 --> 00:03:50.932 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'm sure you're extremely
worried

00:03:50.965 --> 00:03:52.299 position:30% line:83% align:start
but you'll see
that everything

00:03:52.332 --> 00:03:53.467 position:24% line:89% align:start
will turn out fine.

00:03:53.501 --> 00:03:54.869 position:41% line:89% align:start
Sanson.

00:03:54.902 --> 00:03:56.537 position:19% line:83% align:start
You know exactly where
she is, don't you?

00:03:56.571 --> 00:03:57.672 position:41% line:89% align:start
Mm-hmm.

00:03:57.705 --> 00:03:59.707 position:30% line:83% align:start
All right then.
Let's go bring her back.

00:04:14.421 --> 00:04:16.323 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Nadia] Where am I?

00:04:16.356 --> 00:04:19.761 position:19% line:83% align:start
[robotic voice] This is
the satellite city Red Noah.

00:04:19.794 --> 00:04:22.295 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Nadia] Red Noah?

00:04:22.329 --> 00:04:24.331 position:16% line:89% align:start
[robotic voice] Welcome,

00:04:24.364 --> 00:04:26.734 position:27% line:83% align:start
rightful heir of
the Toris Megistos,

00:04:26.768 --> 00:04:27.702 position:30% line:89% align:start
Princess Nadia.

00:04:27.735 --> 00:04:29.369 position:35% line:89% align:start
[Nadia] Me?

00:04:29.402 --> 00:04:31.706 position:30% line:83% align:start
[robotic voice]
We have awaited your arrival

00:04:31.739 --> 00:04:35.910 position:16% line:83% align:start
so that we may hand down
the history of Atlantis to you.

00:04:37.812 --> 00:04:39.479 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Nadia] But who are you?

00:04:39.514 --> 00:04:41.749 position:30% line:83% align:start
[robotic voice]
Creations of the inhabitants

00:04:41.783 --> 00:04:44.752 position:24% line:89% align:start
of the M78 Nebula.

00:04:44.786 --> 00:04:47.420 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Nadia] The M78 Nebula?

00:04:48.856 --> 00:04:51.793 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:05:14.982 --> 00:05:16.784 position:7% line:89% align:start
[robotic voice] The M78 Nebula

00:05:16.818 --> 00:05:20.922 position:21% line:89% align:start
is 277.5 light years

00:05:20.955 --> 00:05:23.858 position:7% line:89% align:start
from the Earth's solar system.

00:05:23.891 --> 00:05:27.862 position:7% line:83% align:start
The people of Atlantis made an
emergency landing on the Earth

00:05:27.895 --> 00:05:31.699 position:21% line:89% align:start
2,400,000 years ago.

00:05:36.571 --> 00:05:39.507 position:13% line:83% align:start
The Atlanteans were forced
to live on Earth

00:05:39.540 --> 00:05:42.777 position:19% line:83% align:start
but they were unable to
return to their own star.

00:05:42.810 --> 00:05:46.981 position:7% line:83% align:start
Here, they created as powerful
a civilization as they could.

00:05:47.014 --> 00:05:49.482 position:30% line:83% align:start
They did so to
banish the darkness

00:05:49.517 --> 00:05:52.452 position:16% line:89% align:start
from this untamed planet.

00:05:54.555 --> 00:05:57.959 position:27% line:83% align:start
But in so doing,
they made an unfortunate error.

00:06:01.662 --> 00:06:04.632 position:38% line:83% align:start
They used
their technological marvels

00:06:04.665 --> 00:06:06.901 position:24% line:89% align:start
to wage holy wars.

00:06:06.934 --> 00:06:09.170 position:33% line:89% align:start
As a result,

00:06:09.203 --> 00:06:12.874 position:24% line:83% align:start
their great cities
were reduced to desolation.

00:06:12.907 --> 00:06:16.443 position:35% line:83% align:start
Afterwards,
the few survivors of Atlantis

00:06:16.476 --> 00:06:20.982 position:16% line:83% align:start
built a new civilization
on the continent of the Pangaea.

00:06:21.015 --> 00:06:23.951 position:27% line:83% align:start
That civilization
was once again destroyed

00:06:23.985 --> 00:06:26.153 position:19% line:89% align:start
by the hunger for war.

00:06:29.557 --> 00:06:33.728 position:38% line:83% align:start
You have
the power of Toris Megistos.

00:06:33.761 --> 00:06:35.830 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Nadia] Toris Megistos?

00:06:36.697 --> 00:06:38.532 position:7% line:89% align:start
[robotic voice] You see, Nadia,

00:06:38.566 --> 00:06:42.536 position:7% line:83% align:start
the Blue Water was once called
the Philosopher's Stone.

00:06:42.570 --> 00:06:45.539 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Nadia] Does this stone
contain such awesome power?

00:06:46.641 --> 00:06:48.042 position:27% line:83% align:start
[robotic voice]
That I cannot say.

00:06:50.544 --> 00:06:53.080 position:19% line:83% align:start
The rightful possessor
of the Toris Megistos

00:06:53.114 --> 00:06:56.083 position:13% line:89% align:start
can either be god or devil.

00:06:56.117 --> 00:06:59.220 position:30% line:83% align:start
They will know
the beginning of all life.

00:06:59.253 --> 00:07:01.689 position:41% line:83% align:start
[Nadia]
And I have inherited this power?

00:07:02.690 --> 00:07:06.694 position:30% line:83% align:start
[robotic voice]
Yes. You are not a human being.

00:07:06.727 --> 00:07:08.963 position:24% line:83% align:start
You are the heir of
the Atlantean dynasty

00:07:08.996 --> 00:07:11.198 position:24% line:89% align:start
of the M78 Nebula.

00:07:13.567 --> 00:07:15.903 position:41% line:83% align:start
[Nadia]
I am not a human being.

00:07:15.937 --> 00:07:18.205 position:24% line:89% align:start
I am an Atlantean.

00:07:20.875 --> 00:07:23.577 position:16% line:83% align:start
-[Sanson] Be careful now.
-[Hanson] And come back quickly.

00:07:23.611 --> 00:07:25.246 position:30% line:89% align:start
I'm very sorry.

00:07:25.279 --> 00:07:27.181 position:35% line:83% align:start
We all know
that you're the only one

00:07:27.214 --> 00:07:29.917 position:24% line:83% align:start
who can find Nadia
and bring her back to us.

00:07:29.951 --> 00:07:31.819 position:21% line:89% align:start
Thank you, everyone.

00:07:31.852 --> 00:07:34.088 position:19% line:89% align:start
[all] Good luck, Jean!

00:07:34.121 --> 00:07:35.455 position:33% line:89% align:start
[King purrs]

00:07:37.124 --> 00:07:39.794 position:5% line:89% align:start
Well now, I say we start packing

00:07:39.827 --> 00:07:42.530 position:13% line:83% align:start
so we'll be ready to leave
when Jean and Nadia come back.

00:07:42.563 --> 00:07:44.031 position:7% line:89% align:start
Um, what happened to the wind?

00:07:44.065 --> 00:07:46.100 position:33% line:89% align:start
[gasps] Wind?

00:07:46.133 --> 00:07:48.269 position:30% line:83% align:start
I don't see any
birds or insects around.

00:07:48.302 --> 00:07:51.038 position:13% line:83% align:start
There aren't any mosquitoes
nibbling at us today either.

00:07:51.072 --> 00:07:54.075 position:30% line:89% align:start
Hmm, hmm, hmm.

00:07:54.108 --> 00:07:55.910 position:33% line:83% align:start
-[King purrs]
-Here it comes.

00:07:55.943 --> 00:07:58.646 position:35% line:89% align:start
[rumbling]

00:08:01.916 --> 00:08:03.718 position:35% line:89% align:start
[screaming]

00:08:06.921 --> 00:08:09.557 position:16% line:89% align:start
[sighs] Oh, my goodness.

00:08:09.590 --> 00:08:11.959 position:41% line:83% align:start
What is
happening to this island?

00:08:11.993 --> 00:08:14.762 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[groans]
-Huh?

00:08:14.795 --> 00:08:17.531 position:16% line:83% align:start
[gasps] Please excuse me.
I really didn't mean to do that.

00:08:17.565 --> 00:08:19.667 position:30% line:89% align:start
[punch landing]

00:08:22.737 --> 00:08:25.573 position:38% line:89% align:start
[screams]

00:08:27.942 --> 00:08:30.011 position:19% line:83% align:start
Bonnie Prince Charlie,
look over there.

00:08:30.044 --> 00:08:32.246 position:24% line:89% align:start
Oh, what is it now?

00:08:33.748 --> 00:08:35.716 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[gasps]
-What are you looking at that?

00:08:35.750 --> 00:08:37.985 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Hanson] The hillside
slid into the ocean.

00:08:38.019 --> 00:08:39.820 position:24% line:89% align:start
That's impossible.

00:08:39.854 --> 00:08:43.290 position:24% line:83% align:start
Even so, I'm afraid
this will only be the beginning.

00:08:45.793 --> 00:08:48.295 position:16% line:83% align:start
What a strong earthquake.
Are you all right?

00:08:50.731 --> 00:08:52.666 position:21% line:83% align:start
This island is simply
a manmade ship

00:08:52.700 --> 00:08:54.168 position:27% line:83% align:start
that was created
by someone.

00:08:55.836 --> 00:08:58.739 position:27% line:89% align:start
[device whirring]

00:08:59.173 --> 00:09:01.275 position:41% line:83% align:start
[Nadia]
What--what's happening?

00:09:01.308 --> 00:09:04.045 position:16% line:83% align:start
[robotic voice] A control
device has been activated.

00:09:04.078 --> 00:09:06.580 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Nadia] Control device?

00:09:06.614 --> 00:09:09.750 position:10% line:83% align:start
[robotic voice] Red Noah has
awaited your arrival

00:09:09.784 --> 00:09:10.785 position:24% line:89% align:start
with great urgency.

00:09:11.318 --> 00:09:12.987 position:35% line:89% align:start
[Nadia] Me?

00:09:13.020 --> 00:09:15.322 position:13% line:83% align:start
[robotic voice] Allow me to
be your guide, Princess Nadia.

00:09:18.025 --> 00:09:19.693 position:16% line:89% align:start
Just wait for me, Nadia.

00:09:22.196 --> 00:09:23.230 position:44% line:89% align:start
Wow!

00:09:25.032 --> 00:09:27.268 position:19% line:83% align:start
I should be able to get
into that opening below.

00:09:27.301 --> 00:09:28.169 position:35% line:89% align:start
All right.

00:09:33.774 --> 00:09:34.809 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:09:35.976 --> 00:09:37.745 position:38% line:89% align:start
[screams]

00:09:37.778 --> 00:09:39.346 position:38% line:89% align:start
[groans]

00:09:40.915 --> 00:09:41.982 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:09:42.016 --> 00:09:43.684 position:16% line:89% align:start
Not my precious balloon.

00:09:43.717 --> 00:09:45.753 position:33% line:83% align:start
Do we have to
mend it all over again?

00:09:48.322 --> 00:09:50.758 position:38% line:89% align:start
[groans]

00:09:53.060 --> 00:09:54.295 position:44% line:89% align:start
Jean!

00:09:56.831 --> 00:09:57.465 position:35% line:89% align:start
[Jean] Huh?

00:09:58.833 --> 00:10:00.734 position:7% line:89% align:start
It looks like our boy is safe.

00:10:00.768 --> 00:10:02.403 position:16% line:83% align:start
And the balloon is still
completely intact.

00:10:02.436 --> 00:10:05.239 position:10% line:83% align:start
And it looks like he's trying
to tell us something.

00:10:06.440 --> 00:10:08.976 position:27% line:89% align:start
Stop the Gratan!

00:10:09.009 --> 00:10:10.911 position:13% line:89% align:start
He said we should stop now.

00:10:10.945 --> 00:10:14.148 position:27% line:89% align:start
[tires screeches]

00:10:22.089 --> 00:10:25.025 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Nadia] What are
you going to do with me?

00:10:25.059 --> 00:10:27.328 position:7% line:83% align:start
[robotic voice] We are going to
take you

00:10:27.361 --> 00:10:28.996 position:13% line:89% align:start
to the Kingdom of Atlantis.

00:10:29.029 --> 00:10:30.631 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Nadia] Atlantis?

00:10:31.232 --> 00:10:32.399 position:16% line:89% align:start
[robotic voice] Correct.

00:10:32.433 --> 00:10:35.035 position:41% line:83% align:start
[Nadia]
But that kingdom lies in ruins.

00:10:35.069 --> 00:10:37.071 position:7% line:89% align:start
No one is supposed to be there.

00:10:37.104 --> 00:10:39.874 position:30% line:83% align:start
[robotic voice]
No. You are to be there.

00:10:39.907 --> 00:10:42.042 position:35% line:89% align:start
[thudding]

00:10:42.076 --> 00:10:44.945 position:21% line:83% align:start
You think Nadia is on
the other side of this wall?

00:10:44.979 --> 00:10:47.915 position:5% line:83% align:start
There was a barrier exactly like
this one in Gargoyle's compound.

00:10:47.948 --> 00:10:49.750 position:41% line:89% align:start
Nadia.

00:10:49.783 --> 00:10:51.752 position:5% line:83% align:start
So you're saying you think Nadia
has been captured

00:10:51.785 --> 00:10:53.320 position:13% line:89% align:start
by Gargoyle all over again?

00:10:53.988 --> 00:10:57.024 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'm not so sure this was created
by Gargoyle.

00:10:57.057 --> 00:10:59.827 position:21% line:89% align:start
[deep breath, snorts]

00:11:00.327 --> 00:11:02.296 position:16% line:89% align:start
Watch out now! Here I go!

00:11:07.101 --> 00:11:08.469 position:35% line:89% align:start
That hurt.

00:11:08.503 --> 00:11:10.137 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Hanson] Listen up, everybody.

00:11:10.171 --> 00:11:11.005 position:33% line:83% align:start
-[Marie] Huh?
-[Sanson] Hmm?

00:11:13.040 --> 00:11:16.043 position:10% line:83% align:start
I think we're all aware that
this island is quite peculiar.

00:11:16.076 --> 00:11:19.046 position:16% line:83% align:start
To say that it's peculiar
is only scratching the surface.

00:11:19.079 --> 00:11:20.748 position:33% line:89% align:start
[King purrs]

00:11:20.781 --> 00:11:23.184 position:21% line:83% align:start
But even a rough idea
is good enough for now.

00:11:24.018 --> 00:11:26.453 position:5% line:83% align:start
We've been living on this island
for four months

00:11:26.487 --> 00:11:27.988 position:7% line:89% align:start
and we all know it's traveling

00:11:28.022 --> 00:11:29.456 position:19% line:83% align:start
in an east to northeast
direction

00:11:29.490 --> 00:11:32.426 position:27% line:83% align:start
at a speed of one
to ten kilometers a day.

00:11:32.459 --> 00:11:35.296 position:7% line:83% align:start
It's scientifically impossible
but it's happening anyway.

00:11:35.329 --> 00:11:39.466 position:16% line:83% align:start
However, since yesterday
the speed has been increasing,

00:11:39.500 --> 00:11:43.137 position:13% line:83% align:start
which means an entirely new
phenomenon is now taking place,

00:11:43.170 --> 00:11:46.273 position:7% line:83% align:start
which means that we can't tell
what will happen next

00:11:46.307 --> 00:11:48.342 position:33% line:83% align:start
because it's
beyond our knowledge.

00:11:49.043 --> 00:11:51.879 position:10% line:83% align:start
But if you can't rely on any
of your previous data

00:11:51.912 --> 00:11:53.347 position:33% line:83% align:start
then how can
you predict anything?

00:11:53.380 --> 00:11:55.082 position:7% line:89% align:start
With intuition and imagination.

00:11:55.115 --> 00:11:57.151 position:33% line:89% align:start
[group] Huh?

00:11:57.184 --> 00:12:00.254 position:7% line:83% align:start
This situation has excited both
of these elements

00:12:00.287 --> 00:12:01.322 position:27% line:89% align:start
inside my brain.

00:12:02.256 --> 00:12:04.291 position:35% line:83% align:start
The sudden
sinking of the eastern slope,

00:12:04.325 --> 00:12:06.927 position:30% line:83% align:start
the upheaval of
the western sand dune,

00:12:07.494 --> 00:12:11.865 position:16% line:83% align:start
the strange luminescence
in the sky all point to the fact

00:12:11.899 --> 00:12:14.835 position:27% line:83% align:start
that this island
is showing signs of strain.

00:12:16.337 --> 00:12:18.939 position:30% line:89% align:start
[wind blowing]

00:12:18.973 --> 00:12:21.543 position:10% line:83% align:start
Even a child could figure out
what will happen next.

00:12:21.576 --> 00:12:25.112 position:10% line:83% align:start
This entire island is listing
precipitously to the east,

00:12:25.145 --> 00:12:28.882 position:13% line:83% align:start
and if it continues to list
in this manner unabated...

00:12:28.916 --> 00:12:32.253 position:5% line:83% align:start
Then an earthquake like the last
one could happen all over again?

00:12:32.286 --> 00:12:34.488 position:19% line:83% align:start
An earthquake like that
will definitely happen again,

00:12:34.522 --> 00:12:36.390 position:7% line:89% align:start
but that's not the worst of it.

00:12:37.858 --> 00:12:39.059 position:24% line:89% align:start
If we are struck by

00:12:39.093 --> 00:12:41.462 position:27% line:83% align:start
a disturbance of
that magnitude again,

00:12:41.495 --> 00:12:43.931 position:27% line:83% align:start
this island will
sink into the ocean.

00:12:45.332 --> 00:12:47.101 position:35% line:83% align:start
-[rumbling]
-[all screaming]

00:12:50.371 --> 00:12:54.041 position:16% line:89% align:start
â™ª The Secret Blue Water

00:12:56.377 --> 00:12:58.580 position:30% line:83% align:start
[robotic voice]
Release the suction valve.

00:12:58.613 --> 00:13:01.549 position:10% line:89% align:start
Remove all extraneous matter.

00:13:01.583 --> 00:13:03.917 position:16% line:89% align:start
[gasps] What do you mean?

00:13:03.951 --> 00:13:05.553 position:30% line:83% align:start
[robotic voice]
The trees, plants,

00:13:05.587 --> 00:13:07.154 position:16% line:89% align:start
and earth on the surface.

00:13:07.187 --> 00:13:08.389 position:38% line:89% align:start
No. Wait.

00:13:08.422 --> 00:13:10.924 position:21% line:83% align:start
There's still people
living on the surface.

00:13:10.958 --> 00:13:13.360 position:13% line:83% align:start
[robotic voice] Red Noah is
descending

00:13:13.394 --> 00:13:14.828 position:33% line:83% align:start
to a depth of
800 meters.

00:13:15.929 --> 00:13:18.232 position:10% line:89% align:start
It is too late to turn back.

00:13:26.407 --> 00:13:27.441 position:30% line:89% align:start
It's happening.

00:13:27.474 --> 00:13:29.310 position:35% line:89% align:start
[rumbling]

00:13:45.926 --> 00:13:47.094 position:24% line:89% align:start
You must stop this.

00:13:47.127 --> 00:13:49.129 position:16% line:83% align:start
All of my friends will be
destroyed

00:13:49.163 --> 00:13:50.464 position:13% line:89% align:start
if this process continues.

00:13:52.466 --> 00:13:55.102 position:27% line:83% align:start
Why do we have to
submerge into the ocean?

00:13:55.135 --> 00:13:56.970 position:10% line:89% align:start
If this is all because of me,

00:13:57.004 --> 00:13:58.872 position:19% line:83% align:start
then I don't want to go
down there.

00:13:58.906 --> 00:14:02.109 position:16% line:83% align:start
[robotic voice] You must
become the ruler of Atlantis

00:14:02.142 --> 00:14:06.080 position:5% line:83% align:start
in order to guide the lost souls
towards its restoration.

00:14:06.113 --> 00:14:08.415 position:24% line:83% align:start
But must we destroy
other lives

00:14:08.449 --> 00:14:11.118 position:19% line:83% align:start
so that Atlantis may be
restored?

00:14:11.151 --> 00:14:14.154 position:19% line:83% align:start
[robotic voice] We are
entering the critical stage.

00:14:14.188 --> 00:14:16.558 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Nadia] You want me
to be the devil, is that it?

00:14:16.591 --> 00:14:19.059 position:7% line:89% align:start
You're no better than Gargoyle!

00:14:19.093 --> 00:14:21.962 position:13% line:83% align:start
[follower] We have observed
a high energy reading.

00:14:21.995 --> 00:14:24.498 position:13% line:83% align:start
Seven degrees, ten minutes,
north latitude.

00:14:24.532 --> 00:14:29.571 position:5% line:83% align:start
Sixty-two minutes east longitude
at zero hour 43 minutes.

00:14:29.604 --> 00:14:33.207 position:24% line:83% align:start
It is traveling at
19 knots per hour.

00:14:33.240 --> 00:14:35.409 position:38% line:89% align:start
Red Noah.

00:14:35.442 --> 00:14:39.012 position:13% line:83% align:start
The holy fortress has begun
to move at last.

00:14:39.046 --> 00:14:41.148 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Hanson]
Oh. What is all of this stuff?

00:14:41.181 --> 00:14:45.219 position:7% line:83% align:start
My dresses, cosmetics, linens,
dishes, and cookery.

00:14:45.252 --> 00:14:47.689 position:16% line:83% align:start
Pillow sheets, blankets,
and cushiony mats to sleep on.

00:14:47.722 --> 00:14:49.990 position:33% line:83% align:start
A one month's
supply of food and water.

00:14:50.023 --> 00:14:52.292 position:7% line:89% align:start
I just brought a bunch of toys.

00:14:52.326 --> 00:14:54.495 position:33% line:89% align:start
[King purrs]

00:14:54.529 --> 00:14:56.230 position:13% line:89% align:start
It's going to be impossible

00:14:56.263 --> 00:14:58.666 position:10% line:83% align:start
for the Gratan to carry this
kind of load, you guys.

00:14:58.700 --> 00:15:00.535 position:5% line:89% align:start
So keep what you absolutely need

00:15:00.568 --> 00:15:02.537 position:13% line:83% align:start
and leave the rest of this
junk behind.

00:15:02.570 --> 00:15:04.438 position:24% line:83% align:start
[all] Oh, you gotta
be kidding, Hanson.

00:15:04.471 --> 00:15:06.039 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Jean] It's all right.
I'm getting off.

00:15:06.073 --> 00:15:07.542 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:15:07.575 --> 00:15:10.277 position:10% line:83% align:start
Nadia's still waiting for me
somewhere down on that island.

00:15:10.310 --> 00:15:11.713 position:19% line:89% align:start
I must help her escape.

00:15:11.746 --> 00:15:14.948 position:19% line:83% align:start
So the rest of you just
go ahead of us on the Gratan.

00:15:14.982 --> 00:15:16.618 position:27% line:83% align:start
But if you end up
getting stuck down there,

00:15:16.651 --> 00:15:18.452 position:30% line:83% align:start
you're going to
sink with everything else.

00:15:18.485 --> 00:15:21.689 position:10% line:83% align:start
Once I locate Nadia, we will
make our get away on that boat.

00:15:23.691 --> 00:15:25.025 position:33% line:83% align:start
-But, Jean...
-It's my duty

00:15:25.058 --> 00:15:26.628 position:10% line:89% align:start
to protect Nadia from danger.

00:15:26.661 --> 00:15:28.095 position:35% line:89% align:start
I have to.

00:15:30.063 --> 00:15:32.700 position:35% line:83% align:start
-[rumbling]
-[screaming]

00:15:37.304 --> 00:15:40.073 position:13% line:89% align:start
Hurry before time runs out!

00:15:40.441 --> 00:15:43.243 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[grunts]
-Marie wants to help find Nadia.

00:15:43.277 --> 00:15:45.245 position:24% line:83% align:start
You must leave here
with the others, Marie.

00:15:45.279 --> 00:15:48.482 position:35% line:83% align:start
No! I wanna
escape with you and Nadia!

00:15:48.516 --> 00:15:52.219 position:13% line:83% align:start
But if you go away with me,
who's going to protect King?

00:15:52.252 --> 00:15:52.887 position:35% line:89% align:start
All right.

00:15:54.522 --> 00:15:56.423 position:5% line:89% align:start
We will meet you in Africa then.

00:15:58.526 --> 00:15:59.561 position:35% line:89% align:start
Good luck!

00:15:59.594 --> 00:16:02.630 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:16:03.765 --> 00:16:06.601 position:35% line:89% align:start
[rumbling]

00:16:12.239 --> 00:16:13.273 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:16:15.610 --> 00:16:18.145 position:19% line:89% align:start
[rotor blades whirring]

00:16:25.452 --> 00:16:28.021 position:33% line:89% align:start
Jean. Nadia.

00:16:44.204 --> 00:16:47.040 position:35% line:89% align:start
[rumbling]

00:17:04.659 --> 00:17:06.460 position:10% line:89% align:start
I demand that you release me!

00:17:06.493 --> 00:17:09.496 position:10% line:83% align:start
It is my wish to remain above
with my friends!

00:17:10.197 --> 00:17:12.734 position:13% line:89% align:start
What awaits me in Atlantis?

00:17:12.767 --> 00:17:15.637 position:33% line:83% align:start
What good is
the ruler of a dead country?

00:17:15.670 --> 00:17:19.206 position:10% line:83% align:start
It is evil to take the earth
from beneath my friend's feet!

00:17:19.239 --> 00:17:21.809 position:5% line:83% align:start
I will not sacrifice their lives
to your wishes!

00:17:25.513 --> 00:17:27.615 position:30% line:83% align:start
[robotic voice]
We do not understand.

00:17:27.649 --> 00:17:30.350 position:24% line:83% align:start
Why would the heir
to the throne of Atlantis

00:17:30.384 --> 00:17:32.352 position:16% line:89% align:start
wish to live with humans?

00:17:32.386 --> 00:17:36.624 position:7% line:83% align:start
The restoration of the kingdom
is our shared dream.

00:17:36.658 --> 00:17:39.359 position:10% line:89% align:start
Only you can accomplish this

00:17:39.393 --> 00:17:42.730 position:10% line:83% align:start
as the inheritor of the blood
of Atlantis and the Blue Water.

00:17:43.665 --> 00:17:46.133 position:30% line:89% align:start
No! Release me!

00:17:46.166 --> 00:17:47.702 position:35% line:83% align:start
Somebody is
waiting for me outside!

00:17:49.837 --> 00:17:51.271 position:41% line:89% align:start
Nadia!

00:17:53.440 --> 00:17:54.842 position:35% line:89% align:start
[rumbling]

00:17:54.876 --> 00:17:55.743 position:38% line:89% align:start
[screams]

00:18:02.817 --> 00:18:04.217 position:33% line:89% align:start
What's that?

00:18:05.285 --> 00:18:07.555 position:21% line:83% align:start
I can get back to her
through these tunnels.

00:18:08.723 --> 00:18:11.224 position:27% line:83% align:start
I do not want to
remain here with you.

00:18:12.159 --> 00:18:14.696 position:5% line:89% align:start
I will determine my own destiny.

00:18:14.729 --> 00:18:16.731 position:7% line:89% align:start
I no longer need anyone's help.

00:18:16.764 --> 00:18:20.868 position:13% line:83% align:start
If my fate changes, it will
be the results of own actions.

00:18:20.902 --> 00:18:22.837 position:10% line:89% align:start
[robotic voice] Your destiny

00:18:22.870 --> 00:18:25.205 position:7% line:83% align:start
is to be the rightful ruler of
Atlantis.

00:18:25.238 --> 00:18:26.708 position:19% line:89% align:start
Stop saying that to me!

00:18:26.741 --> 00:18:28.408 position:16% line:89% align:start
I was born here on Earth!

00:18:28.442 --> 00:18:30.678 position:35% line:83% align:start
I'm on this
island only by accident!

00:18:30.712 --> 00:18:33.413 position:5% line:89% align:start
[robotic voice] Not by accident.

00:18:33.447 --> 00:18:37.685 position:21% line:83% align:start
It was the Blue Water
that brought you here, Nadia.

00:18:37.719 --> 00:18:40.755 position:35% line:83% align:start
Huh? It is
responsible for everything.

00:18:40.788 --> 00:18:44.559 position:16% line:83% align:start
For blood-soaked war and
the taking of innocent lives.

00:18:44.592 --> 00:18:46.928 position:30% line:83% align:start
[robotic voice]
That cannot be helped.

00:18:46.961 --> 00:18:50.698 position:16% line:83% align:start
It is simply your fate as
a direct descendant of Atlantis.

00:18:50.732 --> 00:18:53.601 position:30% line:83% align:start
A person's fate
is not so simplistic!

00:18:53.635 --> 00:18:56.938 position:13% line:83% align:start
All I want is to return to
the place where I was born!

00:18:56.971 --> 00:18:59.641 position:27% line:83% align:start
If the Blue Water
refuses to allow me that,

00:18:59.674 --> 00:19:01.341 position:10% line:89% align:start
then I'd rather not have it!

00:19:02.543 --> 00:19:03.711 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:19:06.313 --> 00:19:09.149 position:38% line:89% align:start
[panting]

00:19:18.526 --> 00:19:20.193 position:41% line:89% align:start
Nadia!

00:19:22.897 --> 00:19:25.800 position:33% line:89% align:start
Nadia! Nadia!

00:19:26.801 --> 00:19:28.836 position:41% line:89% align:start
[pants]

00:19:35.275 --> 00:19:37.645 position:21% line:89% align:start
Oh, Nadia! [whimpers]

00:19:38.880 --> 00:19:43.885 position:24% line:89% align:start
[screaming] Nadia!

00:19:43.918 --> 00:19:44.952 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:19:48.488 --> 00:19:49.957 position:27% line:89% align:start
He's come for me?

00:19:56.329 --> 00:19:59.600 position:33% line:89% align:start
[sobs] Jean!

00:19:59.634 --> 00:20:00.902 position:30% line:89% align:start
Oh, I'm sorry.

00:20:00.935 --> 00:20:02.704 position:7% line:89% align:start
[robotic voice] Princess Nadia.

00:20:07.675 --> 00:20:11.646 position:5% line:83% align:start
Is there something more precious
to you than the Blue Water?

00:20:15.550 --> 00:20:16.383 position:35% line:89% align:start
What is it?

00:20:18.351 --> 00:20:21.321 position:33% line:83% align:start
Do you refuse
your fate for this desire?

00:20:35.837 --> 00:20:37.839 position:21% line:89% align:start
Come, Princess Nadia.

00:20:38.740 --> 00:20:42.944 position:10% line:83% align:start
I will take you to Tartessos,
the place where you were born.

00:20:42.977 --> 00:20:44.979 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Nadia] Tartessos?

00:20:45.012 --> 00:20:47.414 position:7% line:83% align:start
[robotic voice] The Blue Water
will guide you there.

00:20:48.616 --> 00:20:49.984 position:27% line:89% align:start
Simply follow it.

00:20:53.420 --> 00:20:56.423 position:38% line:83% align:start
However,
you cannot escape your fate.

00:20:58.358 --> 00:21:01.028 position:35% line:83% align:start
I shall see
you again, Princess Nadia.

00:21:11.939 --> 00:21:14.509 position:21% line:83% align:start
[follower] The target
has begun to submerge.

00:21:14.542 --> 00:21:16.711 position:24% line:83% align:start
It is currently in
the Indian Ocean

00:21:16.744 --> 00:21:18.713 position:7% line:89% align:start
on a west-by-southwest heading.

00:21:18.746 --> 00:21:20.014 position:33% line:89% align:start
What's that?

00:21:20.047 --> 00:21:21.549 position:10% line:89% align:start
It's moving toward Atlantis.

00:21:21.582 --> 00:21:24.585 position:33% line:83% align:start
Garfish 33 is
presently pursuing it.

00:21:29.857 --> 00:21:31.626 position:35% line:89% align:start
Oh, Nadia.

00:21:31.659 --> 00:21:32.927 position:27% line:89% align:start
Our last voyage.

00:21:33.928 --> 00:21:35.663 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Nadia] Jean?

00:21:35.696 --> 00:21:38.032 position:35% line:89% align:start
Huh? Nadia?

00:21:38.065 --> 00:21:40.367 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Nadia] Don't open your eyes
until I tell you to.

00:21:40.400 --> 00:21:41.068 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah!

00:21:42.402 --> 00:21:45.072 position:35% line:83% align:start
Nadia! I've
looked all over for you.

00:21:45.106 --> 00:21:46.941 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Nadia] I said close your eyes.

00:21:54.715 --> 00:21:55.983 position:30% line:89% align:start
Where are you?

00:21:56.017 --> 00:21:57.618 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Nadia] Right here.

00:21:57.652 --> 00:21:58.586 position:35% line:89% align:start
[Jean] Huh?

00:22:02.422 --> 00:22:04.759 position:30% line:83% align:start
I knew you were
going to come back for me.

00:22:04.792 --> 00:22:05.960 position:44% line:89% align:start
Jean!

00:22:09.697 --> 00:22:10.665 position:41% line:89% align:start
Nadia.

00:22:14.836 --> 00:22:18.005 position:13% line:83% align:start
The island is sinking fast
so we better get out now.

00:22:19.106 --> 00:22:20.074 position:41% line:89% align:start
Mm-hmm.

00:22:23.144 --> 00:22:25.980 position:38% line:89% align:start
[panting]

00:22:29.851 --> 00:22:30.918 position:10% line:89% align:start
Look how much of it has sunk.

00:22:30.952 --> 00:22:32.086 position:35% line:89% align:start
[rumbling]

00:22:32.119 --> 00:22:34.121 position:19% line:89% align:start
Hurry! We have to move!

00:22:39.492 --> 00:22:40.928 position:35% line:83% align:start
-[rumbling]
-[screaming]

00:22:40.962 --> 00:22:42.362 position:41% line:89% align:start
Nadia!

00:22:44.966 --> 00:22:47.635 position:35% line:89% align:start
[grunting]

00:22:47.668 --> 00:22:49.070 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Nadia] Jean!

00:22:49.103 --> 00:22:50.705 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Jean] Hold tight!

00:22:54.809 --> 00:22:57.477 position:35% line:89% align:start
[screaming]

00:23:00.514 --> 00:23:01.782 position:35% line:89% align:start
The Gratan!

00:23:01.816 --> 00:23:04.652 position:27% line:89% align:start
[waves crashing]

00:23:08.623 --> 00:23:10.992 position:5% line:89% align:start
Well, that a narrow escape, boy.

00:23:11.025 --> 00:23:12.727 position:5% line:89% align:start
Thanks for coming to our rescue.

00:23:12.760 --> 00:23:14.629 position:13% line:89% align:start
Think nothing of it, Jean.

00:23:14.662 --> 00:23:16.463 position:38% line:83% align:start
We're all
friends here, aren't we?

00:23:16.496 --> 00:23:18.532 position:35% line:89% align:start
[laughter]

00:23:18.566 --> 00:23:19.466 position:41% line:89% align:start
Nadia!

00:23:21.535 --> 00:23:22.603 position:41% line:89% align:start
Marie.

00:23:25.740 --> 00:23:27.808 position:38% line:89% align:start
Oh, King.

00:23:27.842 --> 00:23:31.212 position:33% line:89% align:start
[King purrs]

00:23:31.245 --> 00:23:33.814 position:38% line:83% align:start
What now?
It's almost gone for good.

00:23:33.848 --> 00:23:36.684 position:27% line:89% align:start
[waves crashing]

00:23:39.854 --> 00:23:41.488 position:33% line:89% align:start
And so it is.

00:23:41.522 --> 00:23:42.890 position:16% line:89% align:start
Fare thee well, Red Noah.

00:23:42.924 --> 00:23:44.792 position:30% line:89% align:start
Red Noah? What?

00:23:44.825 --> 00:23:46.193 position:13% line:89% align:start
That was the island's name.

00:23:46.227 --> 00:23:47.662 position:41% line:89% align:start
I see.

00:23:47.695 --> 00:23:49.630 position:33% line:89% align:start
[gasps] Look!

00:23:49.664 --> 00:23:51.132 position:27% line:83% align:start
-It's a Garfish!
-It's a Garfish!

00:23:55.870 --> 00:23:56.704 position:21% line:89% align:start
[singing in Japanese]

